    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for the discerning collector is a superlative 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, presented in concours-level condition. This 996.2 variant is powered by a mid-mounted 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus timing and lift, delivering linear power through a Getrag 6-speed manual transaxle. Mechanical integrity is paramount; this example features a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a pristine rear main seal. Utilizing the wider Turbo-chassis architecture, the vehicle employs an advanced all-wheel-drive system and a factory-spec suspension tuned for high-speed stability and neutral cornering. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc calipers clamping cross-drilled, ventilated rotors, showing zero signs of thermal stress. Every bushing, link, and synchro operates with factory precision, ensuring a visceral and mechanically pure driving experience.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
